@notice opens a position for 'quote' * 'leverage'

@dev this function can also be used to increase, decrease, close, or reverse-open an existing position
@dev delegatecalls to the PositionManager library

@param amm — collection
@param side — long or short
@param quote — margin
@param leverage — leverage
@param baseLimit — min base amount to receive / max base amount to spend

@notice closes a position 

@dev caller must have a pre-existing position to close
@dev delegatecalls to the PositionManager library

@param amm — collection
@param size — absolute size to close
@param quoteLimit — min quote amount to receive / max quote amount to spend

@notice executes a trigger order to close a position on behalf of a trader

@dev call will revert if trigger order conditions are unmet
@dev caller receives keeper fee
@dev delegatecalls to the PositionManager library

@param id — id of trigger order

@notice removes caller's 'shares' from 'amm'
@notice realizes LP's impermanent position, by merging it into caller's taker position

@dev returns margin to caller if there is no impermanent position
@dev returns margin to caller if there is no remaining liquidity in AMM

@param addedMargin — margin to add to permanent position (can be zero) so trader can decide margin ratio of new position

@notice creates a limit 'order' for caller

@dev delegatecalls to the OrderCreator library

@return id — id of new limit order

@notice creates multiple limit '_orders' for caller

@dev delegatecalls to the OrderCreator library

@return ids — ids of new limit orders

@notice creates a trigger 'order' for caller

@dev delegatecalls to the OrderCreator library

@return id — id of new trigger order

@notice liquidates 'amm' position 'size' of 'liquidatee' 
@notice merges 'liquidatee' position 'size' with caller

@dev will revert if liquidatee is not liquidatable
@dev may result in a decrease, close, or reverse-open for caller
@dev partial liquidations will revert if liquidatee has bad debt
@dev if full liquidation, caller will get 2.5% of liquidatee notional position 
     added to new position
@dev if partial liquidation, caller will get 2.5% / 2 of liquidatee notional position
     added to new position
@dev will revert if caller's position is liquidatable after merge
@dev delegatecalls to the PositionMerger library

@param margin — margin to add to new caller position (can be zero)

@notice liquidates 'liquidatee' LP position in 'amm'
@notice merges 'liquidatee' impermanent position with caller

@dev will revert if liquidatee impermanent position is not liquidatable
@dev will revert if caller's position is liquidatable after merge
@dev may result in a decrease, close, or reverse-open for caller
@dev caller will get 2.5% of liquidatee impermanent notional position 

@param margin — margin to add to new caller position (can be zero)

@notice sets "validAMM" to true or false for protocol

@dev will revert if amm is active and setting to invalid
@dev only callable by owner

@notice performs ADL trade on underwater 'maker' and above water 'taker' positions
        in 'amm' for 'size'

@dev will revert if maker has no bad debt or if taker has insufficient margin
@dev only callable by owner

